INSERT INTO `essay_exam_questions` (`id`, `exam_id`, `question`, `correct_answer`, `marks`, `created_at`) VALUES
(2, 27, 'what is light', 'light is that which illuminates', 20, '2026-01-10 01:42:01'),
(3, 27, 'what is science', 'a body of knowledge obtained by observation and testing of facts', 30, '2026-01-10 01:42:31'),
(4, 27, 'what is a noun', 'the name of  person , animal place or things', 30, '2026-01-10 01:43:02'),
(6, 28, 'wqqeew', 'ewea', 10, '2026-01-10 10:49:15'),
(12, 32, 'The participatory paradigm aligns most closely with the social work value of _______________ because it empowers communities as co-researchers.', 'social justice / empowerment / self-determination', 2, '2026-03-02 19:17:52'),
(13, 32, 'In Nigerian research ethics, approval from the _______________ is mandatory for all health-related research.', 'National Health Research Ethics Committee (NHREC)', 2, '2026-03-02 19:18:35'),
(14, 32, 'Informed consent in Nigeria must navigate both individual consent and _______________ -level permission from elders and traditional leaders.', 'community', 2, '2026-03-02 19:19:14'),
(15, 32, 'The principle of _______________ requires that research benefits flow both ways, not just from community to researcher.', 'reciprocity', 2, '2026-03-02 19:19:44'),
(16, 32, 'A strong CBR research question must be community-driven and _______________-oriented.', 'action', 2, '2026-03-02 19:20:54'),
(17, 32, 'A _______________ of Understanding (MOU) formalizes partnership agreements between researchers and communities.', 'Memorandum', 2, '2026-03-02 19:38:04'),
(18, 32, 'When selecting co-researchers, considerations include representativeness, credibility, and _______________.', 'availability / willingness', 2, '2026-03-02 19:38:35'),
(19, 32, 'In Northern Nigeria, focus groups on sensitive topics often require _______________-separate sessions.', 'gender', 2, '2026-03-02 19:39:09'),
(20, 32, 'A _______________-structured interview guide allows for flexibility and probing based on participant responses.', 'semi', 2, '2026-03-02 19:39:36'),
(21, 32, 'A researcher\'s identity, background, and biases that shape what they see and interpret is called _______________.', 'positionality', 2, '2026-03-02 19:40:10'),
(22, 32, 'Systematic observation of a community by walking through it with community guides is called a _______________ walk.', 'transect', 2, '2026-03-02 19:40:54'),
(23, 32, 'In Nigeria, _______________-based sampling at markets, churches, and motor parks is often more effective than random sampling.', 'venue', 2, '2026-03-02 19:41:39'),
(24, 32, 'When quantitative surveys are used in Nigerian communities, they should be complemented by _______________ methods to explain the meaning behind numbers.', 'qualitative', 2, '2026-03-02 19:42:22'),
(25, 32, 'The PAR cycle consists of Planning, Action, Observation, and _______________', 'reflection', 2, '2026-03-02 19:43:21'),
(26, 32, 'The _______________ environmental monitoring project in Rivers State combined local water testing with community testimonies to advocate for oil spill cleanup.', 'Ogoni', 2, '2026-03-02 19:43:56'),
(27, 32, 'Using multiple methods strategically so they strengthen each other is called methodological', 'triangulation', 2, '2026-03-02 19:44:26'),
(28, 39, 'The study of the movement of chemicals through the body, including absorption, distribution, metabolism, and excretion, is known as ____________________.', 'Toxicokinetics (or ADME)', 2, '2026-03-02 20:16:29'),
(29, 39, 'In the Niger Delta, gas flaring releases contaminants primarily through the ____________________ route of exposure.', 'Inhalation', 2, '2026-03-02 20:19:04'),
(30, 39, 'A chemical that has an LDâ‚…â‚€ value of 5 mg/kg is considered ____________________ (more/less) toxic than one with an LDâ‚…â‚€ of 500 mg/kg.', 'More', 2, '2026-03-02 20:19:34'),
(31, 39, 'The process by which the body converts a chemical into a more water-soluble form for elimination is called ____________________.', 'Metabolism (or biotransformation)', 2, '2026-03-02 20:20:24'),
(32, 39, 'When benzene is converted to benzene epoxide in the liver, this process is known as ____________________.', 'Bioactivation', 2, '2026-03-02 20:20:55'),
(33, 39, 'The highest dose of a chemical that causes no statistically significant adverse effect in a test population is abbreviated as ____________________.', 'NOAEL', 2, '2026-03-02 20:21:27'),
(34, 39, 'In environmental science, the complete pathway from contaminant source to exposed individual is described by the ____________________ model.', 'Source-Pathway-Receptor', 2, '2026-03-02 20:21:55'),
(35, 39, 'Children are more vulnerable to lead exposure partly because of increased ____________________ (hand-to-mouth activity/body weight).', 'Hand-to-mouth activity', 2, '2026-03-02 20:22:44'),
(36, 39, 'A chemical that causes cancer is called a ____________________.', 'Carcinogen', 2, '2026-03-02 20:23:20'),
(8, 33, 'qwqawqwqw', 'qwqwqwqw', 10, '2026-01-23 10:17:04'),
(9, 34, 'qwqwqw', 'qwqw', 10, '2026-01-23 10:19:59'),
(10, 36, 'sasasasas', 'sasasa', 10, '2026-02-16 09:41:47'),
(11, 32, 'The relationship between the researcher and what can be known is called _______________.', 'epistemology', 2, '2026-03-02 19:17:16'),
(37, 39, 'Blood lead level is an example of a biomarker of ____________________.', 'Exposure', 2, '2026-03-02 20:23:47'),
(38, 39, 'For genotoxic carcinogens, risk assessment typically uses a ____________________ (threshold/non-threshold) model.', 'Non-threshold', 2, '2026-03-02 20:24:20'),
(39, 39, 'In the Uvwie exposure calculation, a child\'s daily intake is expressed in units of ____________________.', 'Î¼g/kg/day (or mg/kg/day)', 2, '2026-03-02 20:25:01'),
(40, 39, 'The Nigerian regulatory body responsible for environmental standards and enforcement is ____________________.', 'NESREA', 2, '2026-03-02 20:25:24'),
(42, 39, 'Uncertainty in risk assessment refers to ____________________, while variability refers to differences among individuals in a population.', 'Lack of knowledge / incomplete data', 2, '2026-03-02 20:29:39'),
(43, 39, 'The third step in the four-step risk assessment framework after hazard identification and dose-response assessment is ____________________.', 'Exposure Assessment', 2, '2026-03-02 20:30:14'),
(44, 39, 'A chemical that causes heritable changes in DNA is classified as a ____________________.', 'Mutagen', 2, '2026-03-02 20:31:00'),
(45, 39, 'In the Ekpan community case study, the presence of DNA adducts in 30% of adults indicates ____________________ (exposure/effect/susceptibility).', 'Effect', 2, '2026-03-02 20:33:45'),
(46, 42, 'The international framework that guides global DRR efforts from 2015 to 2030 is called the ____________________.', 'Sendai Framework', 2, '2026-03-03 17:00:48'),
(47, 42, 'Social workers contribute to DRR by conducting participatory assessments that identify both vulnerabilities and community ____________________.', 'capacities/strengths', 2, '2026-03-03 17:01:10'),
(48, 42, 'The condition of people, infrastructure, and assets being located in hazard-prone areas is termed ____________________.', 'exposure', 2, '2026-03-03 17:01:34'),
(49, 42, 'In the Pressure and Release (PAR) model, the progression of vulnerability moves from root causes to dynamic pressures and finally to ____________________.', 'unsafe conditions', 2, '2026-03-03 17:02:00'),
(50, 42, 'When a community has strong kinship networks that provide shelter during displacement, this is an example of social ____________________.', 'capacity', 2, '2026-03-03 17:02:25'),
(51, 42, 'The four Priorities for Action of the Sendai Framework are: Understanding Risk, Strengthening Governance, Investing in DRR, and Enhancing ____________________.', 'Preparedness', 2, '2026-03-03 17:02:52'),
(52, 42, 'SDG 11 focuses on making cities and human settlements inclusive, safe, resilient, and ____________________.', 'sustainable', 2, '2026-03-03 17:03:19'),
(53, 42, 'DRR is considered the first line of ____________________ to climate change, as it builds resilience to climate-related hazards.', 'adaptation', 2, '2026-03-03 17:03:44'),
(54, 42, 'A disaster that develops gradually over time, such as drought or desertification, is classified as ____________________-onset.', 'slow', 2, '2026-03-03 17:04:11'),
(55, 42, 'The process of identifying the nature and extent of risk by analyzing potential hazards and evaluating conditions of vulnerability is called disaster ____________________.', 'risk assessment', 2, '2026-03-03 17:04:35'),
(56, 42, 'In the Niger Delta, oil spills are classified as ____________________/industrial hazards.', 'technological', 2, '2026-03-03 17:05:01'),
(57, 42, 'CBDRM emphasizes that communities should be active ____________________ in DRR, not just beneficiaries.', 'participants/partners', 2, '2026-03-03 17:05:25'),
(58, 42, 'A participatory process that maps both community vulnerabilities and existing strengths is called a Vulnerability and ____________________ Assessment (VCA).', 'capacity', 2, '2026-03-03 17:05:54'),
(59, 42, 'The agency responsible for oil spill detection and response in Nigeria is ____________________.', 'NOSDRA', 2, '2026-03-03 17:06:25'),
(60, 42, 'The gap between national DRR policies and their implementation at the local level is often referred to as the ____________________ gap.', 'implementation', 2, '2026-03-03 17:06:56'),
