(406, 87, 'The _________ conntrol system represents the first and most cost-effective line of waste minimisation in drilling operations by removing solids before disposal becomes necessary', 'solid', 2, '2026-03-19 19:27:17'),
(407, 87, 'Shale shakers primarily remove _________ and _________ particles from drilling fluids based on screen separation efficiency', 'large cuttings; coarse solids', 2, '2026-03-19 19:27:57'),
(408, 87, 'Hydrocyclones utilise _________ force to separate solids, with desanders targeting _________ particles and desilters removing _________ particles.', 'centrifugal; medium-sized; finer', 2, '2026-03-19 19:29:14'),
(409, 87, '4.	Decanter centrifuges operate as the _________ stage of the solids control chain, producing cleaner mud and _________ cuttings', 'final polishing; drier', 2, '2026-03-19 19:31:07'),
(410, 87, 'Landfarming relies on natural processes such as _________, _________, and _________ to degrade hydrocarbons in drilling waste.', 'microorganisms; sunlight; aeration', 2, '2026-03-19 19:32:02'),
(411, 87, 'Bioremediation can be classified into _________, which involves nutrient addition, and _________, which involves the introduction of specialised microorganisms.', 'biostimulation; bioaugmentation', 2, '2026-03-19 19:33:09'),
(412, 87, 'Cement solidification is not considered a true treatment method because contaminants are _________ rather than chemically degraded', 'immobilised (or trapped)', 2, '2026-03-19 19:35:28'),
(413, 87, 'Engineered landfills incorporate _________ systems, _________ collection mechanisms, and _________ wells to ensure environmental protection', 'liners; leachate; monitoring', 2, '2026-03-19 19:36:56'),
(414, 87, 'In offshore operations, the _________ method involves transporting waste in containers to centralised treatment facilities, despite risks of _________ during transit', 'skip-and-ship; spills', 2, '2026-03-19 19:38:32'),
(415, 87, 'Thermal desorption units (TDU) typically operate within a temperature range of _________ to _________ Â°C to volatilise hydrocarbons from drill cuttings', '300; 550', 2, '2026-03-19 19:40:10'),
(416, 87, 'Thermo-mechanical technologies such as Rotomill generate heat predominantly through _________, thereby reducing overall _________ consumption compared to conventional TDU systems', 'friction; energy', 2, '2026-03-19 19:41:31'),
(417, 87, 'Cuttings re-injection (CRI) requires careful control of _________ pressure to ensure fracture propagation without compromising _________ integrity', 'injection; well', 2, '2026-03-19 19:42:25'),
(418, 87, 'Biosurfactants are preferred in drilling waste treatment because they are _________, exhibit low _________, and enhance oil mobilisation', 'biodegradable; toxicity', 2, '2026-03-19 19:43:04'),
(419, 87, 'In circular economy approaches, recovered _________ from drilling waste can be reused as a weighting material, thereby reducing dependence on _________ imports', 'barite; imported', 2, '2026-03-19 19:43:52'),
