(85, 96, 30, 2, 'CENTER FOR WASTE MANAGEMENT AND SUSTAINABLE RESOURCES\r\nTEST QUESTIONS FOR ESW 812 2025/2026 ACADEMICSESSION\r\nINSTRUCTIONS: ANSWER ALL QUESTIONS\r\nDURATION 30MINS\r\nNAME OF LECTURER: DR:CROSSDALE- OVWIDO .J\r\nFill-in-the-gap questions on Community Engagement and Participatory Development, suitable for undergraduate or postgraduate level:\r\n\r\nFill-in-the-Gap Questions\r\n\r\nCommunity engagement refers to the process of working collaboratively with ________ to address issues affecting their well-being.\r\n\r\nParticipatory development emphasizes the active involvement of ________ in decision-making processes.\r\n\r\nThe principle of ________ ensures that all stakeholders have equal opportunities to contribute in development projects.\r\n\r\n________ is the process of enabling communities to gain control over their own development.\r\n\r\nA key tool used in participatory development is ________ rural appraisal (PRA).\r\n\r\nCommunity engagement helps to build ________ between development agencies and local populations.\r\n\r\n________ analysis is used to identify individuals or groups affected by a project.\r\n\r\nThe bottom-up approach in development prioritizes the views of ________ rather than external experts.\r\n\r\n________ participation occurs when people are involved only as a formality without real influence.\r\n\r\nSustainable development is achieved when community members take ________ of projects.\r\n\r\n________ mapping is a participatory tool used to identify community resources and assets.\r\n\r\nEffective community engagement requires good ________ skills to ensure proper information flow.\r\n\r\n________ development focuses on improving the quality of life of people within a specific locality.\r\n\r\nPower ________ can influence the level of participation among different groups in a community.\r\n\r\nMonitoring and evaluation in participatory development often involve ________ from community members.', 0, '2026-03-19 10:00:00', '2026-03-19 10:30:00', 0, '2026-03-18 12:35:36'),
(86, 97, 30, 2, 'CENTER FOR WASTE MANAGEMENT AND SUSTAINABLE RESOURCES\r\nTEST QUESTIONS FOR ESW 813 2025/2026 ACADEMICSESSION\r\nENVIRONMENTAL JUSTICE AND HUMAN RIGHTS\r\nINSTRUCTIONS: ANSWER ALL QUESTIONS\r\nDURATION 30MINS\r\nNAME OF LECTURER: DR:CROSSDALE- OVWIDO .J\r\nFill-in-the-gap questions on Community Engagement and Participatory Development, suitable for undergraduate or postgraduate level:\r\n\r\nFill-in-the-Gap Questions\r\n\r\nfill-in-the-gap questions on Environmental Justice and Human Rights, designed to be analytical and conceptually rigorous:\r\nFill-in-the-Gap Questions (PhD Level)\r\n\r\nEnvironmental justice addresses the fair distribution of environmental ________ and ________ across different social groups.\r\n\r\nThe concept of environmental justice emerged prominently in the ________ during the 1980s as a response to environmental racism.\r\n\r\nEnvironmental racism refers to the disproportionate exposure of marginalized communities to ________ hazards.\r\n\r\nThe principle of ________ justice emphasizes fairness in environmental decision-making processes.\r\n\r\n________ justice focuses on the equitable distribution of environmental goods and harms.\r\n\r\nThe right to a clean, healthy, and sustainable environment is increasingly recognized as a fundamental ________.\r\n\r\n________ inequality highlights the unequal exposure of vulnerable populations to environmental risks.\r\n\r\nThe ________ Convention ensures public access to environmental information and participation in decision-making.\r\n\r\nClimate justice links climate change impacts with issues of ________ and global inequality.\r\n\r\nThe principle of ________ responsibility recognizes that developed countries have contributed more to environmental degradation.\r\n\r\n________ rights emphasize the protection of indigenous peoples\' relationship with their land and natural resources.\r\n\r\nEnvironmental governance requires ________ accountability to ensure that institutions uphold environmental rights.\r\n\r\nThe concept of ________ development integrates environmental protection with social and economic progress.\r\n\r\n________ vulnerability refers to the susceptibility of certain populations to environmental harm due to socio-economic factors.\r\n\r\nThe United Nations Human Rights Council has recognized environmental degradation as a threat to the enjoyment of ________ rights.', 0, '2026-03-19 09:00:00', '2026-03-19 09:30:00', 0, '2026-03-18 12:50:59'),
