(49, 32, 'In CBR, the community\'s role is best described as:', 'Subjects providing data', 'Passive recipients of research findings', 'Co-researchers and co-creators of knowledge', 'Consumers of academic publications', 'C', 2, '2026-03-02 18:58:54', '2026-03-02 18:58:54'),
(48, 32, 'Which of the following BEST describes the primary goal of CBR?', 'Publishing in academic journals', 'Combining knowledge generation with social action and change', 'Testing theoretical hypotheses', 'Maintaining researcher objectivity and distance', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 18:57:34', '2026-03-02 18:57:34'),
(46, 36, 'sdass', 'dasda', 'dasd', 'adad', 'ada', 'A', 10, '2026-02-16 09:41:35', '2026-02-16 09:41:35'),
(47, 32, 'Community-Based Research (CBR) differs from traditional research primarily because it:', 'Uses only qualitative methods', 'Requires university ethics approval', 'Equitably involves community partners throughout the research process', 'Focuses exclusively on health outcomes', 'C', 2, '2026-03-02 18:54:25', '2026-03-02 18:54:25'),
(50, 32, 'The ontological position of positivism holds that:', 'Reality is socially constructed and multiple', 'There is one objective reality that can be measured', 'Reality is shaped by power and oppression', 'Reality exists only in the mind of the researcher', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:00:02', '2026-03-02 19:00:02'),
(51, 32, 'A researcher conducting life-history interviews to understand the lived experiences of market women in Onitsha is operating within which paradigm?', 'Positivist', 'Interpretivist/Constructivist', 'Critical theory', 'Post-positivist', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:01:32', '2026-03-02 19:01:32'),
(52, 32, 'Which paradigm is considered the philosophical home of Community-Based Research because it explicitly addresses power and aims for social transformation?', 'Positivism', 'Interpretivism', 'Participatory/Critical paradigm', 'Empiricism', 'C', 2, '2026-03-02 19:02:37', '2026-03-02 19:02:37'),
(53, 32, 'According to Guba and Lincoln (1994), a research paradigm answers three fundamental questions. Which of the following is NOT one of them?', 'Ontology â€“ What is the nature of reality?', 'Epistemology â€“ What is the relationship between the researcher and what can be known?', 'Methodology â€“ How do we gain knowledge?', 'Economics â€“ What is the cost of research?', 'D', 2, '2026-03-02 19:03:40', '2026-03-02 19:03:40'),
(54, 32, 'In Nigerian community research, informed consent should be understood as:', 'A one-time signature on a form', 'An ongoing process of dialogue and negotiation', 'Verbal agreement only', 'Permission from the university ethics board only', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:04:44', '2026-03-02 19:04:44'),
(55, 32, 'The principle of reciprocity in Nigerian CBR means:', 'Paying all participants the same amount', 'Ensuring mutual benefit and leaving communities stronger than found', 'Exchanging research findings for access', 'Publishing results in local newspapers', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:05:41', '2026-03-02 19:05:41'),
(56, 32, 'Which body provides national ethics oversight for health-related research in Nigeria?', 'Nigerian Universities Commission (NUC)', 'National Health Research Ethics Committee (NHREC)', 'National Population Commission (NPC)', 'Federal Ministry of Education', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:06:34', '2026-03-02 19:06:34'),
(57, 32, 'A researcher discovers that their community co-researcher is sharing sensitive information outside the research team. This represents a failure of:', 'Procedural ethics only', 'Situational and relational ethics', 'Sampling strategy', 'Data analysis', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:07:36', '2026-03-02 19:07:36'),
(58, 32, 'Which of the following is a characteristic of a strong CBR research question?', 'Complex academic jargon to impress reviewers', 'Community-driven, action-oriented, and collaborative', 'Focused only on theoretical contribution', 'Designed without community input for objectivity', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:08:30', '2026-03-02 19:08:30'),
(59, 32, 'A researcher working with a community that has strong traditional leadership and existing decision-making structures should consider which partnership model?', 'Outsider-led research team', 'Community Advisory Board with traditional council', 'Individual researcher autonomy', 'Online survey only', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:09:21', '2026-03-02 19:09:21'),
(60, 32, 'When selecting community co-researchers, which consideration is MOST important?', 'Their availability to work for free', 'Their representativeness and credibility in the community', 'Their English language proficiency', 'Their university degree status', 'B', 2, '2026-03-02 19:10:45', '2026-03-02 19:10:45'),
