(137, 'AKOMAYE PETER BENSON', '', 'jeraw2@gmail.com', '08055512812', 'km 4 Refinery rd,By Mega Hilton Hotel Ekpan- Warri, Delta State', '7', 'PgD WASTE MANAGEMENT-Environmental Management & Toxicology Dept.- Federal  University Of  Petroleum Resources Efurrun (FUPRE) Delta State.', 'Entrepreneurship and Enterprise management- SEF 2019  Oxford SBS-UK                                                   \r\n2019 \r\nï‚· Fields operations Mgr / Project Supervisor ï‚®  Environmental Services-B2 Oil & Gas Projects Ltd    2009 - 2016 \r\nï‚· Lab. Analyst / Microbiologist ï‚®Global Environmental Consultants Ltd, Forcados operations  \r\n2008- 2018 \r\nï‚· Environmental Scientist /P Consultant/ Sewage &Wastewater Innovations.ï‚® Jaymak Energy Ltd, Nig2012 - Date \r\nï‚·  Science Teacher/ Biologyï‚®NYSC-Onicha Ugbo Girls Secondary School, Delta State. \r\nï‚· Laboratory Trainee /IT Studentâ€”Cross River Basin Dev. Authority(Federal min. Of Water res.) Calabar .           \r\n2007 â€“ 2008 \r\n2004', '\r\n\r\nMy interest in environmental and social development stems from an experience while supervising a sewage treatment project in Warri, where I observed firsthand the adverse effects of polluted water on community health. That incident shaped my conviction that environmental issues extend beyond science and technologyâ€”they are deeply social, influencing livelihoods and human dignity.\r\n\r\nAs an Environmental Scientist with over a decade of experience in the oil and gas sector, I have contributed to environmental compliance monitoring, wastewater management, and post-impact assessments for organizations such as SPDC, Chevron, and GEC Nigeria Ltd. These experiences have strengthened my appreciation of the link between sustainable environmental management and social welfare.\r\n\r\nWith a B.Sc. in Microbiology and a Postgraduate Diploma in Waste Management from FUPRE, I seek to advance my knowledge through the MSc in **Environmental Social Work and Development** at **CWMR, FUPRE**. The programme aligns with my professional goal of integrating social work principles into environmental practice, particularly in the areas of community engagement, environmental justice, and sustainable development.\r\n\r\nI am confident that this programme will equip me with the theoretical and practical tools needed to design interventions that protect the environment while improving the quality of life in affected communities.\r\n', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_68f3632ae292f6.77798813.pdf', '$2y$10$oWSgJYQ52iRrGBrkur87lu4DSol1RU7kNDR4T4ls6ywqMf6MMNpPu', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_68f3632b3ea7e7.05250981.jpg', 'applied', 'not suspended', NULL, '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(138, 'IMELDA BLANKSON', 'imeldablankson4u@cwmsrfupre.com.ng', 'imeldablankson4u@gmail.com', '+2348035313687', '10 CIRCULAR ROAD, ELEKAHIA HOUSING ESTATE, PORT HARCOURT, NIGERIA', '14', 'MASTERS', 'Over 15 years in supervisory and managerial position managing HSE across different sectors and industries.', 'My academic foundation in Sustainable Waste Management has provided a strong platform for integrating environmental science with social responsibility. Through research and applied projects, I have examined the intersection of Extended Producer Responsibility (EPR), circular resource loops, and value stream optimization as tools for environmental transformation. These studies reinforced my conviction that true sustainability requires more than efficient disposal systemsâ€”it demands community engagement, data-driven innovation, and policies that reshape production and consumption at their roots.\r\n\r\nParallel to my academic growth, my professional experience has nurtured an intimate understanding of how environmental neglect amplifies human vulnerability. Working in different sectors has taught me that waste management is not only an environmental issue but also a social one. Each improperly handled material, each inefficient system, has human consequences. This understanding pushes me to explore waste not merely as a technical problem but as a human systems challenge requiring equity-driven innovation.\r\n\r\nThe research ethos of CWMS, FUPRE, focused on advancing indigenous solutions to waste, energy, and resource management, resonates with my goal to bridge academic theory with actionable policy and practice. I am particularly interested in studying integrated municipal waste systems and circular economy transitions in urban African contexts, where population growth and consumption pressures demand scalable, inclusive models. \r\nMy vision is to contribute to the development of frameworks that align government regulations, private sector responsibility, and community participation into a unified sustainability ecosystem.\r\n\r\nLooking forward, I see my PhD journey not as an academic destination but as a launchpad for transformative environmental leadership. My ambition is to lead multidisciplinary projects that close the loop between waste generation, resource recovery, and public healthâ€”ultimately shaping communities that view waste as a resource rather than a residue. \r\n\r\nThrough research collaboration, policy advocacy, and technological integration, I hope to strengthen Africaâ€™s role in the global sustainability movement.\r\n\r\nIn every step of my professional and academic journey, I have embraced the belief that sustainable progress begins where people and the planet meet. \r\nCWMS, FUPRE provides the environment, mentorship, and research infrastructure to actualize this vision. With a deep sense of purpose and preparation, I am ready to contribute to groundbreaking research and to the creation of resilient waste systems that will define the environmental future of our world.', NULL, '$2y$10$muIjkROABd4x7GtlAXVyBORo93FRO67qEVD0/F26j4p3J4Cx9165K', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_68f647046d0d14.93920225.jpeg', 'admitted', 'not suspended', 'RFU/2025/9171', '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(139, 'OLAOLUWA OLAWE', 'olawe_laozy@cwmsrfupre.com.ng', 'olawe_laozy@yahoo.com', '08063474367', '10, Seun Nwachi Street, Isheri, Lagos', '14', 'M.Sc', 'Starich Recycling Technology Co. Ltd [Director of Operations] Contract\r\nOnitsha, Anambra State. (2023- Present)\r\nWaste Box [Executive Director]\r\nSouth Region, Nigeria. (2021-Present)\r\n', 'I have decided to pursue a Phd Waste Management after a good deal of self evaluation. My decision of pursuing this program followed naturally after carefully considering my academic background, the areas of my interest and my ultimate professional experience in Recycling/Waste management.\r\n\r\nEnvironmental issues like Climate change is the most serious issue of the world today. The present environmental situation has intrigued my interest in pursuing waste management, this led me searching for a prestigious institute to horn my skills in waste management analysis and i found Federal University of Petroleum Resources,Effurun, Delta State which is known to be the right amalgamation of learning from field excursions and practical.\r\n\r\nI strongly believe in few values, which are hard work that is necessity to produce results, discipline that is necessity to finish task before deadlines and persistence that is necessity to sail through unproductive periods. My attempt throughout has been to inculcate these qualities in.', NULL, '$2y$10$aNoWRuzA7o2QMyqRlXF5puuQo/E3dYX9qRiDViSw40Lti1aLLZBbO', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_68f8bd0ce9c859.05353728.jpg', 'admitted', 'not suspended', 'RFU/2025/8322', '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(140, 'ENENMOH, Lawrence Ebialim', 'ichristopher75@cwmsrfupre.com.ng', 'ichristopher75@yahoo.com', '07032972498', '298, Cadastral Zone, Durumi, Abuja. Nigeria', '6', 'BSc', 'Demonstrated progressively responsible leadership qualities culminating in leadership/ supervising of the Agencyâ€™s activities in various places of postings. These were the Oando depots, Total, Oando Total Joint venture, all in Lagos and the NNPC depot in Ibadan and the NNPC regional office in Lagos. In other words, career has spanned through the South western region and the North central regions.', 'I am applying for the Safety Program in Waste Management because of my strong interest in environmental protection and public health. My research on â€œAssessment of Healthcare Waste Management Practices in Warri and Environsâ€ exposed me to the risks of poor waste handling and the importance of safety in waste operations. This experience inspired me to pursue further training to improve my understanding of safe and sustainable waste management practices.', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_6901a900890537.46811813.pdf', '$2y$10$WlFSCZwukCnnBTLeD0gyB.uqMHnqGNaxDDDSb7I7M6ScYF6XUdkX6', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_6901a901e894f0.23315425.jpg', 'admitted', 'not suspended', 'RFU/2025/1637', '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(141, 'Agadagba Joan', '', 'edirinjoan@gmail.com', '08135951583', '1 Omafuaire Close, Olughor Layout. Ogbumoro. Effurun', '14', 'Maters', 'So many', 'Nil', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_692937b225c4f9.38769536.pdf', '$2y$10$Cx7.RWGeG5kiQmSrM2e8IefElW3D0cbpwl7r/7pTJb8p7ewskItbG', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_692937b3316eb0.06521586.jpeg', 'applied', 'not suspended', NULL, '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(142, 'Nwokafor chukwunyere venantius', 'chuksvenantius@cwmsrfupre.com.ng', 'chuksvenantius@yahoo.com', '08037868015', 'House 7 D close CBS great estate lugbe Abuja', '7', 'HND  architecture with distinction', 'Over 20 years work experience with reputable organization. ', 'I strongly believe that I have all it takes to run this program which will in turn help me achieve my dream of participating in community development', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_6904938dc9e142.17950723.pdf', '$2y$10$cVwqEpEi7FthuFQR6g1anODiE0CXJH2ojwVjuheWAzJ6adPz.sbA.', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_6904938dccb239.40517037.jpg', 'admitted', 'not suspended', 'RFU/2025/6597', '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(143, 'Dr Akinyemi ogunkeyede', 'ogunkeyedeakinyemi@cwmsrfupre.com.ng', 'ogunkeyedeakinyemi@gmail.com', '09030223041', 'Centre For Waste Management And Sustainable Resources, Fupre', '6', 'B.Sc.', 'zxsdv cevexas', 'c ggsacwdawcf3a', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_691b7619ad76f3.87449875.pdf', '$2y$10$hB89kajnwGeXmM/VE8ZU9OGnM7MZuGdtsaUA8L6zAg3QlFucwT2ei', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_691b761a1ae0d9.15891628.jpg', 'admitted', 'not suspended', 'RFU/2025/0532', '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(144, 'Matilda Iwunor', 'mkiwunor@cwmsrfupre.com.ng', 'mkiwunor@gmail.com', '+491630045932', '12B, ADEGBENLE STREET, CHEVVY VIEW ESTATE, LEKKI, LAGOS, NIGERIA.', '15', 'MSc', 'I volunteered as a community worker in Pitakwa, Rivers State after my MSc.', 'Hailing from Southern Nigeria, I have been intrigued by the intricate relationship between our environment and our communities: how the environment and its resources sustain us and contribute immensely to our source of livelihood.\r\n\r\nThis led me to pursue a Bachelorâ€™s degree in Industrial Chemistry and a Masterâ€™s in Environmental Assessment and Management, and as I seek to take the next step in my career, I hereby apply for the PhD program in Environmental Social Work and Community Development.\r\n\r\nDuring my undergraduate studies, I not only delved into chemical processes but also began to understand how industrial practices can impact the world around us.\r\n\r\nI visited communities during a project about sustainable practices in the aviation industry and it opened my eyes to the pressing need for solutions that address both environmental and social issues. This realization laid the groundwork for my masterâ€™s thesis, where I investigated the effects of the aviation industry on neighbouring communities, which revealed the disparities that exist in our society.\r\n\r\nWhile pursuing my MSc, I had the opportunity to engage with communities directly, which was rewarding.Â \r\n\r\nIn addition, I worked on a project examining water quality in water bodies (close to residential areas), which are mainly for domesticÂ use. I discussed with local residents and hearing their stories motivated me to advocate for those whose voices are often overlooked. It became clear to me that effective solutions require not just scientific expertise, but also a good understanding of the community\'s needs.\r\n\r\nIÂ  believe that real change happens at the grassroots level, where community members have the power to shape their environmental futures. Itâ€™s inspiring to see how collective effort can empower people and foster sustainable practices.\r\n\r\nThis PhD program resonates deeply with my goals. I am particularly drawn to your interdisciplinary approach, which I believe is crucial for addressing the complexities of environmental challenges.\r\n\r\nI am eager to learn and to engage in research that explores participatory frameworks, ensuring that community perspectives are at the heart of environmental solutions.\r\n\r\nI aspire to work with NGOs or within governmental organizations to promote policies that empower communities.\r\n\r\nIn pursuing this PhD, I hope to gain the skills and insights necessary to lead initiatives that prioritize both ecological health and social justice.\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, I am excited about the path that lies ahead and the opportunity to contribute to the field of Environmental Social Work and Community Development. I am committed to making a meaningful difference, and I believe that my journey has uniquely prepared me for this endeavor.Â \r\n\r\nThank you for considering my application.', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_691da85515b314.30155201.pdf', '$2y$10$CFnRQJ.tu.4O0ApjWQBLbOBLSnbDX7KC/tJ6ZaiRAkoGN97uU1vfG', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_691da8567061a4.31346762.jpg', 'admitted', 'not suspended', 'RFU/2025/8417', '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(145, 'OGUORI-OKODASO Ejiroghene', '', 'okodaso.ejiro@gmail.com', '08159757831', 'No. 107 Orhuwhorun Road, Ekete   ', '14', 'M.Sc ', 'About 20years of service as an Environmental Health Officer with the Delta State Waste Management Board. ', 'Sustainable Waste Management: a result of continuous improvement in proper waste management procedures and policies.  ', NULL, '$2y$10$0uKgmWTb9sVadD9hrxsfnuxLlmOD0WoES3dSDrsN4zhvEr/AJBKgi', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_697244de9b2e26.52173542.jpg', 'applied', 'not suspended', NULL, '2026-01-28 15:39:46', '{\"level_id\":3,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L3S2'),
(146, 'ELEXDON TECH ERT', 'contactvictorndu@elexdontech.com', 'contactvictorndu@elexdontech.com', '08185609124', 'elexdon tech', '1', 'hnd', 'wesaasd', 'asdasas', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_68538fa9071e83.33516813.pdf', '$2y$10$JSvrORUoNuxgal9AVvCrGeCmJtOVjGX4sUD8KN4Hu1mujoePqHG8G', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_68538fa90759f3.16649979.gif', 'admitted', 'not suspended', 'RFU/2025/4187', '2026-01-28 15:40:58', '{\"level_id\":4,\"semester_id\":1}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L4S1'),
(165, 'ELEXDON TECH ERT', 'contactvictorndu@elexdontech.com', 'contactvictorndu@elexdontech.com', '08185609124', 'elexdon tech', '1', 'hnd', 'wesaasd', 'asdasas', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_68538fa9071e83.33516813.pdf', '$2y$10$JSvrORUoNuxgal9AVvCrGeCmJtOVjGX4sUD8KN4Hu1mujoePqHG8G', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_68538fa90759f3.16649979.gif', 'admitted', 'not suspended', 'RFU/2025/4187', '2026-01-28 15:52:10', '{\"level_id\":4,\"semester_id\":2}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'current'),
(147, 'Lemuel Ossai Ifuwe', 'lemuelossaiifuwe@gmail.com', 'lemuelossaiifuwe@gmail.com', '07035495169', '3b Nigercat link road off refinery road ekpan', '1', 'test', 'testtest', 'test', 'uploads/students_applications/app_file_68a4c8846e6691.99585037.pdf', '$2y$10$eRNLf/KphpT25DvGMvTtVu3cTtPOrky.HQgE.j4SUixv.4uFnsr6G', '', 0.00, 'uploads/proof_of_payments/payment_proof_68a4c8846e7543.50657410.jpg', 'admitted', 'suspended', 'RFU/2025/4003', '2026-01-28 15:40:58', '{\"level_id\":4,\"semester_id\":1}', '[{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 1, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 2, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 3, \"semester_id\": 2},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 1},{\"level_id\": 4, \"semester_id\": 2}]', 'L4S1'),
